description: Putin proposed Andrei Belousov, who until recently served as the first deputy prime minister, to replace Sergei Shoigu in a Cabinet shakeup.
title: Putin replaces his defense minister as he starts his 5th term in office

description: The solar storm that's pushing sightings of the Northern Lights to lower latitudes is forecast to continue into the coming days, but its impact has likely peaked.
title: There's still a chance to see the Northern Lights from lower latitudes

description: From California to North Carolina, students staged chants and walkouts over the weekend in protest of Israel's ongoing military offensive in Gaza.
title: Student protests caused mostly minor disruptions at several graduation ceremonies

description: Hundreds of Native American tribes are getting money from lawsuit settlements with opioid companies. Some are investing the new funds in traditional healing practices to treat addiction.
title: A tribe in Maine is using opioid settlement funds on a sweat lodge to treat addiction

description: After initiation rites – including circumcision – the boys leave their families to take charge of the herds, driving them high into the mountains. It's a way of life that climate change is testing.
title: Kenya's Samburu boys share a sacred bond. Why one teen broke with the brotherhood

description: Afuá, a remote town in the Brazilian Amazon, banned motor vehicles over 20 years ago. Writer Mac Margolis and photographer Stefan Kolumban paid the town a visit to see what life is like.
title: A car-free town in the Amazon serves lessons for pedaling to net zero emissions

description: After weeks of preparation, crews are scheduled to conduct a controlled demolition Sunday to break down the largest remaining span of the collapsed Francis Scott Key Bridge in Maryland.
title: Controlled demolition planned at Baltimore bridge collapse site
